sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist
    participant Dashboard as ODH Dashboard<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS<br/>OAuth
    participant NotebookCtrl as Notebook Controller<br/>Kubernetes API
    participant Notebook as Jupyter Notebook<br/>8080/TCP HTTPS<br/>OAuth Proxy
    participant MLflow as MLflow Server<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS<br/>K8s Auth
    participant ModelReg as Model Registry<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS<br/>kube-rbac-proxy
    participant TrainingOp as Training Operator<br/>Kubernetes API
    participant TrainingJob as PyTorchJob Pods<br/>Multi-node<br/>Gang Scheduling
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS<br/>AWS IAM
    participant KServe as KServe Controller<br/>Kubernetes API
    participant ModelCtrl as ODH Model Controller<br/>Kubernetes API
    participant Inference as InferenceService<br/>8000/TCP HTTPS<br/>TLS/mTLS
    participant Client as External Client<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over User,Client: Workflow 1: Model Training to Deployment

    User->>Dashboard: Create Notebook via UI<br/>HTTPS (OAuth Bearer)
    Dashboard->>NotebookCtrl: Create Notebook CR<br/>Kubernetes API
    NotebookCtrl->>Notebook: Deploy StatefulSet + OAuth Proxy<br/>Kubernetes API
    Notebook-->>User: Notebook Ready<br/>HTTPS (OAuth)

    User->>Notebook: Develop & Train Model<br/>HTTPS (OAuth)
    Notebook->>TrainingOp: Create PyTorchJob CR<br/>Kubernetes API
    TrainingOp->>TrainingJob: Deploy Distributed Workers<br/>Gang Scheduling
    TrainingJob->>S3: Store Model Artifacts<br/>HTTPS (AWS IAM Auth)
    TrainingJob->>MLflow: Log Metrics/Params<br/>HTTPS (K8s Auth)
    TrainingJob-->>Notebook: Training Complete

    Notebook->>ModelReg: Register Model Metadata<br/>POST /api/model_registry/v1alpha3/models<br/>HTTPS (kube-rbac-proxy)
    ModelReg-->>Notebook: Model ID

    User->>Dashboard: Create InferenceService<br/>HTTPS (OAuth)
    Dashboard->>KServe: Create InferenceService CR<br/>Kubernetes API
    KServe->>ModelCtrl: Trigger Extensions<br/>Watch Event
    ModelCtrl->>KServe: Add Route/NetworkPolicy/KEDA<br/>Kubernetes API
    KServe->>Inference: Deploy Predictor Pods<br/>Kubernetes API
    Inference->>S3: Load Model from Storage<br/>HTTPS (AWS IAM Auth)
    Inference->>ModelReg: Fetch Model Metadata<br/>GET /api/model_registry/v1alpha3/models/{id}<br/>HTTPS (kube-rbac-proxy)
    Inference-->>KServe: Ready

    Client->>Inference: POST /v1/models/{name}:predict<br/>JSON Payload<br/>HTTPS (TLS 1.3, Bearer Token optional)
    Inference-->>Client: Prediction Result<br/>JSON Response

    Note over User,Client: Workflow 2: Feature Engineering to Serving

    participant Feast as Feast Online Server<br/>6566/TCP HTTP<br/>gRPC/HTTP
    participant FeastOffline as Feast Offline Server<br/>8815/TCP HTTP
    participant Redis as Redis<br/>6379/TCP<br/>Optional TLS

    User->>Notebook: Define Features<br/>HTTPS (OAuth)
    Notebook->>FeastOffline: Apply Feature Definitions<br/>HTTP/gRPC
    FeastOffline->>Redis: Materialize Features<br/>Redis Protocol

    TrainingJob->>FeastOffline: Fetch Historical Features<br/>POST /get-historical-features<br/>HTTP/HTTPS
    FeastOffline-->>TrainingJob: Feature Dataset

    Inference->>Feast: Fetch Online Features<br/>POST /get-online-features<br/>gRPC/HTTP
    Feast->>Redis: Query Features<br/>Redis Protocol
    Redis-->>Feast: Feature Values
    Feast-->>Inference: Features for Inference

    Note over User,Client: Workflow 3: ML Pipeline Orchestration

    participant DSP as Data Science Pipelines API<br/>8888/TCP HTTP<br/>Bearer Token
    participant Argo as Argo Workflow Controller<br/>Kubernetes API
    participant Pipeline as Pipeline Pods<br/>Workflow Tasks

    User->>Dashboard: Submit Pipeline<br/>HTTPS (OAuth)
    Dashboard->>DSP: Create Pipeline Run<br/>POST /apis/v2beta1/runs<br/>HTTP (Bearer)
    DSP->>Argo: Create Workflow CR<br/>Kubernetes API
    Argo->>Pipeline: Launch Task Pods<br/>Kubernetes API
    Pipeline->>TrainingOp: Create TrainJob CR<br/>Kubernetes API
    TrainingOp->>TrainingJob: Deploy Training Workers<br/>Kubernetes API
    TrainingJob->>S3: Store Artifacts<br/>HTTPS (AWS IAM)
    TrainingJob-->>Pipeline: Task Complete
    Pipeline->>KServe: Create InferenceService CR<br/>Kubernetes API
    KServe->>Inference: Deploy Model<br/>Kubernetes API
    Inference-->>Pipeline: Deployment Ready
    Pipeline-->>DSP: Pipeline Status Update<br/>Kubernetes API
    DSP-->>Dashboard: Pipeline Complete

    Note over User,Client: Workflow 4: Model Monitoring with TrustyAI

    participant TrustyAI as TrustyAI Service<br/>8080/TCP HTTPS<br/>Istio mTLS
    participant Postgres as PostgreSQL<br/>5432/TCP<br/>Optional TLS
    participant Prometheus as Prometheus<br/>9090/TCP HTTP

    User->>Dashboard: Create TrustyAI Service<br/>HTTPS (OAuth)
    Dashboard->>TrustyAI: Deploy TrustyAI<br/>Kubernetes API
    TrustyAI->>KServe: Patch InferenceService<br/>Add Payload Logger<br/>Kubernetes API

    Client->>Inference: Inference Request<br/>POST /v1/models/{name}:predict<br/>HTTPS
    Inference->>TrustyAI: Log Request/Response<br/>HTTP (Istio mTLS)
    TrustyAI->>Postgres: Persist Inference Data<br/>PostgreSQL Protocol
    Inference-->>Client: Prediction

    Prometheus->>TrustyAI: Scrape Metrics<br/>GET /metrics<br/>HTTP
    TrustyAI-->>Prometheus: Fairness/Drift Metrics
    User->>Dashboard: View Metrics<br/>HTTPS (OAuth)
